0 = k \frac{q}{ h^2} - k \frac{Q}{(r + h)^2}  
vs  
\[0 = k \left(\left(\frac{ q_1}{ h^2}\right) - \left(\frac{ q_2}{ \left(r + h\right)^2\right)\right) \]
